	   <tr><td colspan=2>HAIL!<br><br>Below is an account of my experience hunting Ancients/Elders in their caves on the Thurdagin side.&nbsp;&nbsp;A total of 115 Wurms were killed and the loot per kill is recorded below.  I've included stats on items dropped and the appropriate quest reward for no-drop quest items.<br><br>I started this killin fresh into level 39 and with 115 Wurm kills under my belt I will say that these guys are a brute to bring down.  However, in that span of time I reached hell 40!  Fortunately as a cleric it was easy to find a partner and one that ensnares is perfect for these beasts (Druid/Ranger w/Ensnare, Necro/SK w/Dooming Darkness or any other class that can slow the movement of the creature).  <br><br>The pull strategy that appeared to work best is to go in and ensnare one, then let it come fully out of the cave to avoid Elder wanderers who will venture just outside tunnel and turn around in front of the entrance and go back in.  Once out of the wanderers agro range, the next step is to fear it and nuke or beat on it.  They are so huge you can still hit them from a nice distance. Ensnare/Fear/Kill worked 115 of 118 times, the other three where link deaths otherwise it would have been 118/118.<br><br>Doing this 115 times successfully however, resulted in a whole lot of loot.  A couple notes though, 66 of the 115 had no loot, so don't get discouraged if you kill 5 in a row and get nothing.  It made getting loot feel like you were getting something for your work.  Though a detailed accout is listed below here is the general summary.  Items included as loot but not included in summary below: Words/Runes, Wurm Meat and gems/jewelry.  In every case the Wurm dropped an average of 3-6pp.  The highest I've seen is 8pp and some gold.<br><br>115 Kills<br><br>66 No Loot<br>9 LVL 44 Spells of various classes<br>8 no drop fangs<br>6 no drop claws<br>5 glowing wurm biles<br>5 shardwurm stingers<br>4 white scaled tunics<br>1 shardwurm skin<br><br>KILL BY KILL DETAIL<br><br>1.  Elder    No Loot<br>2.  Ancient  Spell: Enticement of Flame  44 WIZ<br><br>Note- The spell drops were from Ancients only (not sure if Elders drop them if so must be ultra rare) and they are the level 44 NPC Drop only Velious Spells.  The level 50 NPC spell drops are off the Crystal Wurms, deeper inside.<br><br>3.  Elder     Words/Wurm Meat<br>4.  Ancient   No Loot<br>5.  Elder     Shardwurm Claw (no drop)<br><br>Note- Turn in 4 Shardwurm Claws to a Miner in Thurdagin Mines for a Coldain Miner Pick.  Caution, this weapon is No Drop and for small races only<br><br>Coldain Miner Pick<br>1H Slash  Att 29  DLY  12  Sta +7<br>Effect: Velium Shards (12dd)<br>Class: War Pal RNG SHD BRD ROG<br>Race: ELF HIE DEF DWF HFL GNM<br><br>6.  Elder   Words<br>7.  Elder   Glowing Wurm Bile (no drop)<br><br>Note- The glowing Wurm Bile is an uncommon drop and used in the 5th Shawl Quest.  You need five total and can actually see the Wurms who have it.  They are brighter than the other ones and to know for sure, observe the cave walls, if light is reflecting off the wall, it has a glowing bile.  This is why I came here in the first place, 1 bile down 4 to go.<br><br>8.  Elder    No Loot<br>9.  Ancient  Shardwurm Skin<br><br>Note- The Shardwurm Skin is nice Lowbie caster gear (an upgrade from Najena's Flowing Black Robe).  The interesting thing about this item is that when worn by a caster they look more like a monk or druid.  On a Gnome, it looks like a little black leather jacket (a mini fonzie).<br><br>Sharwurm Skin<br>AC 13  INT +4  Mana +1<br>Class: NEC WIZ ENC MAG<br>Race: All<br><br>10.  Elder  No Loot<br>11.  Elder  Fang (no drop)<br><br>Note- The Shardwurm Fangs are used in a Kael quest.  If Giants hate you it would be difficult to do the quest.  However, this is a good way to get Giant faction up and a nice reward in return.<br><br>12.  Elder   Words<br>13.  Ancient Spell:  Boon of Garou Lvl 44 ENC<br>14.  Ancient No Loot<br>15.  Elder   Fang (no drop)<br>16.  Elder   No Loot<br>17.  Ancient No Loot<br>18.  Ancient No Loot<br>19.  Ancient No Loot<br>20.  Ancient No Loot<br>21.  Ancient Spell: Cir of Wkening Lnds 44 DRU<br>             Shardwurm Stinger<br><br>Note- The Shardwurm Stinger is secondary slot only piercing weapon.  Nice piercing damage for a dual-weilding rogue.<br><br>Shardwurm Stinger<br>Pierce  Att 40  Dly 10<br>Slot: Secondary Only<br>Class: WAR RNG BRD ROG<br>Race: all<br><br>22.  Ancient No Loot<br>23.  Elder   Wurm Meat<br>24.  Elder   Wurm Meat, Shardwurm Claw, Words<br>25.  Ancient No Loot<br>26.  Elder   No Loot<br>27.  Ancient No Loot<br>28.  Elder   Wurm Meat<br>29.  Ancient No Loot<br>30.  Ancient No Loot<br>31.  Ancient No Loot<br>32.  Ancient No Loot<br>33.  Elder   Fang<br>34.  Ancient No Loot<br>35.  Ancient No Loot<br>36.  Elder   Glowing Bile (#2 yayy),Meat <br>             White Scale Tunic<br><br>Note- The White Scale Tunic is about the equivelant of Najena's Flowing Black Robe in quality and stats and like the Shardwurm Skin makes the caster look like a monk or druid.<br><br>White Scale Tunic<br>AC 8 Int +3  Cold +5<br>Class: NEC WIZ ENC MAG<br>Race: All<br><br>37.  Ancient No Loot<br>38.  Ancient Spell: Boon of Garou 44 ENC<br>39.  Elder   No Loot<br>40.  Elder   No Loot<br>41.  Elder   No Loot<br>42.  Elder   No Loot<br>43.  Ancient No Loot<br>44.  Elder   No Loot<br>45.  Ancient No Loot<br>46.  Elder   No Loot<br>47.  Ancient No Loot<br>48.  Elder   Wurm Meat<br>49.  Elder   No Loot<br>50.  Ancient No Loot<br>51.  Elder   No Loot<br>52.  Ancient Spell: Boon of Garou 44 ENC<br>53.  Elder   No Loot<br>54.  Elder   Shardwurm Claw, Rune<br>55.  Elder   No Loot<br>56.  Ancient Spell: Corporal Empathy 44 NEC<br>                    Stinger<br>57.  Ancient No Loot<br>58.  Ancient No Loot<br>59.  Ancient No Loot<br>60.  Ancient White Scaled Tunic, Shardwurm Claw<br>61.  Ancient Spell: Cir of Wakening Lands 44 DRU <br>62.  Elder   Meat, Words<br>63.  Ancient No Loot<br>64.  Ancient Spell: Cir of Wakening Lands 44 DRU<br>65.  Elder   No Loot<br>66.  Ancient No Loot<br>67.  Ancient Stinger<br>68.  Elder   No Loot<br>69.  Ancient Spell: Boon of Garou 44 ENC<br>70.  Elder   Words<br>71.  Ancient No Loot<br>72.  Elder   Words<br>73.  Ancient White Scaled Tunic<br>74.  Elder   No Loot<br>75.  Ancient No Loot<br>76.  Elder   Fang<br>77.  Ancient No Loot<br>78.  Ancient Spell: Corporal Empathy 44 NEC<br>79.  Ancient No Loot<br>80.  Elder   No Loot<br>81.  Elder   White Scaled Tunic, Words<br>82.  Elder   Wurm Meat<br>83.  Elder   Wurm Meat<br>84.  Elder   No Loot<br>85.  Ancient No Loot<br>86.  Elder   No Loot<br>87.  Ancient No Loot<br>88.  Elder   Fang<br>89.  Elder   Glowing Bile (# 3- Woot!), Fang<br>90.  Elder   Ice of Velious<br>91.  Ancient No Loot<br>92.  Ancient Fang<br>93.  Ancient Stinger<br>94.  Elder   No Loot<br>95.  Ancient Emerald Ring (60pp or so at vendor)<br>96.  Elder   Fang, Words, Meat<br>97.  Ancient No Loot<br>98.  Elder   No Loot<br>99.  Ancient Spell: Elemental Maelstrom 44 MAG<br>100. Ancient Spell: Blast of Poison 44 SHA<br>101. Ancient No Loot<br>102. Ancient No Loot<br>103. Ancient No Loot<br>104. Elder   Glowing Bile (# 4- ONE MORE TO GO!!)<br>105. Elder   No Loot<br>106. Elder   No Loot<br>107. Elder   No Loot<br>108. Ancient No Loot<br>109. Elder   Meat, Words<br>110. Ancient Spell: Enticement of Flame 44 WIZ<br>111. Elder   Stinger, Claw<br>112. Ancient No Loot<br>113. Elder   Bile # 5 (this part done!), Meat<br>114. Ancient Claw<br>115. Ancient No Loot<br><br>Well, with the biles in hand, it's off to master tailoring!  Good luck fighting these guys I've seen them take out peeps over level 50!  Anyone fighting them for fun....well, I guess you can always get a job as a crash test dummy.  It hurts less.<br><br><br>Rwest Mmdee <br>40 Cleric<br>Officer of Fury Fighters<br>Xegony  <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
